  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Qpop is a customer-facing application designed to enhance interaction and engagement at the point of sale through a dedicated touchscreen interface. Always facing the customer, Qpop allows for seamless interaction during the sales process by:</p><ul><li><p>Displaying in-store advertisements and promotions</p></li><li><p>Showing real-time ticket details for customer review</p></li><li><p>Presenting electronic forms and waivers for acknowledgment</p></li><li><p>Capturing electronic signatures for payments via integrated devices</p></li></ul><p>Qpop Companion works with Bluefin integrated payment systems, allowing customers to sign for their transactions on the companion device.</p><h3 id=\"CaptureIntegratedPaymentSignaturesonaQpopCompanion-PreviousSteps\">Previous Steps</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936490516/Pair+a+Qpop+Companion\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936490516\" data-linked-resource-version=\"10\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Pair a Qpop Companion</a></p></li><li><p><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/plugins/servlet/servicedesk/customer/confluence/shim/spaces/SCD/pages/1937014846\" rel=\"nofollow\">Create a Qpop Companion</a></p></li></ul><h3 id=\"CaptureIntegratedPaymentSignaturesonaQpopCompanion-OptionalFeaturesandAdditionalResources\">Optional Features and Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936949331/Send+Custom+Forms+to+Your+Qpop+Companion+Device\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936949331\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Send Custom Forms to a Qpop Companion</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934295157/Integrated+Payment+Processing+-+Start+Here\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934295157\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Integrated Payment Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1937047567/Qpop+Companion+Resources+with+Video\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1937047567\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion Resources</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936654410/Qpop+Companion+Troubleshooting\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936654410\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion Troubleshooting</a></p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936359503/image-20230608-173034.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"CaptureIntegratedPaymentSignaturesonaQpopCompanion-SendPaymentSignaturestoQpop\">Send Payment Signatures to Qpop</h2><p>On the Navigation Bar, go to <strong>Settings</strong> \u2192 <strong>Location Settings</strong>. On the Settings Overview page, there is a list of settings categories in the left column. Click <strong>Payments </strong>to expand the dropdown and then click <strong>Payment Devices</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936359503/image-20230608-173039.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"253\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936359503/image-20230608-173044.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Payment Terminal page, locate the device you want to record signatures with Qpop. Under the Actions column, click the <strong>Edit button</strong>. When editing the payment device settings, on the Signature Source field, select <strong>Qpop Companion</strong> from the dropdown and click the <strong>Require Signature</strong> box. Once you are satisfied with your changes, click <strong>Save</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Payment 3.png\" width=\"760\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936359503/Payment%203.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"522\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936359503/image-20230608-173054.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>When requesting Bluefin card payment in RepairQ, the customer will swipe/insert their card into the PAX device as usual. During the payment process, Qpop will prompt the customer for their signature on the tablet. After signing, the customer will tap <strong>Done Signing</strong> to complete the transaction.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936359503/image-20230608-173105.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
